for new fans (fandom name is neverland!)

0:01 - Minnie. (main vocalist)

0:47 - Miyeon. (main vocalist)

1:57 - Yuqi. (lead vocalist/vocalist, lead dancer, face of the group)
2:27 - Shuhua. (vocalist, visual, maknae)

Miyeon, Soyeon, and Soojin were born in South Korea.
Minnie was born in Thailand.
Yuqi was born in China.
Shuhua was born in Taiwan.

The age order from oldest to youngest: Miyeon, Minnie, Soojin, Soyeon, Yuqi, Shuhua.

They debuted in 2018 with the song “LATATA”. Their first comeback also in 2018 was “HANN (Alone).” They came back again in early 2019 with “Senorita” and “Uh-Oh” in mid-late 2019. They participated in “QUEENDOM” (a survival show) and had a song named “LION”. This is their first comeback in 2020 named “OH MY GOD”. Please support them! :)

For more info go to their kprofiles.

snippet.textDisplay:
It seems like cube is only giving lines to people who can make a 'brand' or 'image' for themselves.
-Soyeon is definitely the most know and easiest to recognize. She portrays a strong personality/character (cool/hip/rapper). 'Don't fuck with me' vibe.
-Soonjin is probably 2nd in line. She's heavily branded as the "sexy" one. She can sing and she can DANCE!
-Minnie seems to be branding herself well lately. She comes off as "dark" and maybe even "discordant" (I think because of her unique voice). She also manages to keep the same type of look. Long hair with something in it(ribbons, color, etc). Always recognizable.

Sadly, Miyeon, Yuqi and Shuhua don't seem to be getting the opportunity to do the same. Each of these girls are clearly talented, but they haven't been able to showcase it in the same way the the other girls have been allowed to.
-Miyeon is main vocalist for a reason. Her vocals are always the best in live performances. She always preforms well. But that's all that they show.
-Yuqi obviously has a unique voice for her image. This gave her a lot of attention when they debuted.. but I feel like cube is letting her fade into the background a little bit. Yuqi seemed like she had an "innocent bad girl" vibe going on at first. But now she mostly just does pretty. Which is wonderful. But Miyeon, Yugi and Shuhua all do pretty now.
-Shuhua is cute! and quirky! I think she could easily brand herself if she was given the airtime and the creative liberty. But.. she is the youngest and still seems like she's being punished for not being 200% fluent in Korean.
